    <p slot="journal">
        Hello. This is the first ever journal on Loveisdancing.com.
    </p>

    <p slot="journal">
        I'm really excited for how the website is turning out. Right now, I'm taking a lot of inspiration from <a href="https://isobelsweb.com" target="_blank">isobelsweb.com</a> and <a href="https://cratre.net" target="_blank">cratre.net</a>. If you don't know them, I highly recommend you check them out. Also <a href="https://kidlucky.online" target="_blank">kidlucky.online</a>, <a href="https://girledm.com">girledm.com</a>, and <a href="https://kimpetras.com" target="_blank">kimpetras.com</a>. <em>Detour</em> came out yesterday and it's soooo fucking good.
    </p>

    <p slot="journal">
        I'm finding this renaissance of like electropop EDM type stuff super inspiring. <em>Love is dancing</em> has been written for almost a year now which is wild... how the fuck has it been that long. And I still haven't put it out. But sooooon!! I have a photoshoot with this wickedly talented photographer named <a href="https://benhburton.com" target="_blank">Ben Burton</a>. We followed each other on Instagram and as soon as I saw he was from Columbus I had to shoot my shot. I would describe his work as intimate and meticulous which are two themes I see in my upcoming EP.
    </p>

    <p slot="journal">
        I don't really know what to write for these blogs, so it's mostly just stream-of-consciousness shit right now. Also, the blog date is listed as yesterday's because that's when I started building the layout, but it took me too long that I never actually started writing anything. I'm also kind of sick today and have no plans, so I figured it'd be a good chill activity. I actually do have to work on something, though. For my senior capstone project I made an <a href="https://Loveisdancing.com/iam" target="_blank">interactive audiovisual machine</a> and someone asked me if I'd be interested in collaborating with local musicians to see how it would react to live music. The issue is I wanted to make it more interactive by having each input or instrument do different things, but I don't have a multi-track input that I can use to test. So I downloaded stems from Isobel's <em>Dear April</em> instead. So I do need to test that out today.
    </p>

    <p slot="journal">
        Anyways, I wanna go on a walk now I think. It's 63 degrees which isn't terrible, but I hope walking will keep me warm. Thanks for reading if you did.
    </p>

